    "body": "Co-authored-by: randgun@github.com hexq0210@github.com\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\npreviously accuracy for kimi-vl-a3b-instruct is no more than 0.05.\r\n\r\nThe Kimi-VL-A3B-Instruct model exhibited severe accuracy issues in the current codebase, with benchmark accuracy no higher than 0.05 (5%) —far below the expected performance baseline. Root cause analysis identified misalignment with prerequisite implementations and missing critical KV cache handling, which rendered the model effectively non-functional for practical use.\r\n\r\n## Modifications\r\nas follows\r\n\r\nThe changes made to the 4 documents are to align them with the prior prerequisite PR. https://github.com/sgl-project/sglang/pull/17007. being coherent with npu version: https://github.com/sgl-project/sglang/pull/16436.\r\nBesides, the changes of forward_batch.token_to_kv_pool.set_kv_buffer is to save kv cache. the accuracy would be 0 without this.\r\nthe change of [python/sglang/srt/hardware_backend/npu/moe/topk.py] is to be consistent with the documentation of operator  npu_moe_gating_top_k, adapting to the operator input.\r\n\r\n## Accuracy Tests\r\nAfter applying the above changes, the model’s accuracy saw a dramatic improvement across all critical execution modes:\r\nEagle Mode: Accuracy reaches at least 0.67 (67%)\r\nGraph Mode: Accuracy reaches at least 0.67 (67%)\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1687\" height=\"142\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/92ba4038-ec67-43c5-b2b3-0bf25260ca73\" />\r\n<img width=\"1612\" height=\"156\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/6674fdcc-213a-4aa9-9512-14dc86059b35\" />\r\n\r\nP.S. prerequisite dependency: custom-ops",
